replies.body:
@clickclack472 - yup grievous wounds key item against mundo
@mysticLlamaz - 1 mundo vs whole team and he kills 2 ppl and walks out unscathed.... dunno about that
@Lexhanatin - my most recent games on shen don't reflect mundo matchups since i rarely take shen into that matchup. 

The specific scenario i was highlighting, which has happened in several of my games, is where Mundo is in our jungle on our side of the map, by himself, with ZERO FEAR of being caught, because he can 1v5.

It wasn't a case of we were focusing the wrong target in a teamfight, it was and constantly is the case where he is the ONLY target as the rest of his team is at their fountain and all 5 of us collapse on him. Chain cc? Yup. Grievous wounds? Yup. Multiple full-damage carries? Yup. GUESS WHO WALKS OUT ALIVE?

Mundo. 

After killing a couple of ppl, he saunters out, unscathed. Full tank, no damage items, able to not only withstand the damage of a whole team but also kill multiple members from said team.

Now in teamfights, obviously you focus their carries, not the Mundo, but... you know... when everyone is getting chunked by a pure tank .... wtf is that?!

Mundo has been over-tuned (and/or counterplay items are under-tuned).
